#: ../en/docs/installation.md:17
msgid "By far the easiest method of installing Qgoda is to use [Docker](https://www.docker.com/):"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/installation.md:19
msgid ""
"1. Install Docker.  On Linux/Unix systems, Docker will be available from\n"
"your package manager.  On Mac OS X you can install Docker with Mac Ports\n"
"or Homebrew.  On Windows, get a pre-compiled binary from\n"
"https://www.docker.com/get-docker."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/installation.md:24
msgid "2. Start Docker.  You may want to start the docker daemon automatically.\n"
"Check your vendor's documentation for that!"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/installation.md:27
msgid ""
"3. In a [shell](http://www.guido-flohr.net/en/command-line/), run\n"
"the command `$ docker run --name qgoda -p 3000:3000 --rm -it -v $(pwd):/data gflohr/qgoda watch`.\n"
"You may have to add the user that runs the command to the group \"docker\"\n"
"if you get an error like \"permission denied\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/installation.md:32
msgid ""
"4. You can create an alias, so that you do not have to type in\n"
"the Docker command-line options all the time.  Depending on your operating system,\n"
"you have to open `~/.bash_profile`, `~/.bashrc`, `~/.alias`, `~/.zshrc`\n"
"or similar and add this line:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/installation.md:37
msgid ""
"```bash\n"
"alias qgoda='docker run --name qgoda -p 3000:3000 --rm -it -v $(pwd):/data gflohr/qgoda'\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/installation.md:41
msgid "With this alias, you can now run all qgoda commands like the native version\n"
"described in this documentation."
msgstr ""

