msgid "This would exclude all files and directories with names starting with an underscore but *not* the directory `_posts`."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:144
msgid "### Exclusion and Inclusion Mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:146
msgid "Search patterns behave slightly different, when they are used for *excluding* files (as opposed to including files).  With pattern lists used for excluding files, you cannot re-include files or directories, when one of their parent directories is already excluded."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:173
msgid "You have to keep in mind that Qgoda has prepended this list with `/_*` (see [@ q.lanchor(name = 'excluding-files') @]).  Line 1 re-includes `_experiments`.  Line 2 excludes all its subdirectories again.  And line 3 selectively re-includes `_experiments/stable`."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:175
msgid "## Slashes"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:177
msgid "### Leading Slashes"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:179
msgid "A leading slash anchors the pattern to the source directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:191
msgid "The first patterns starts with a slash.  It therefore excludes the top-level file `package.json` but it would not exclude `a/b/c/package.json`."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:193
msgid "The second pattern is not anchored to the source directory.  It would therefore match `TODO` as well as `a/TODO` or `a/b/TODO`."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:195
msgid "### Trailing Slashes"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:197
msgid "A trailing slash causes a pattern only to match directories:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:206
msgid "This would exclude `src/lib` *only* if it is a directory.  A regular file `src/lib` would not be affected."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:208
msgid "### Other Slashes"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:210
msgid "Every slash inside a pattern causes the entire file name to be taken into account when matching:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:219
msgid "This would exclude `posts/experiments/dangerous-minds.md`.  It does *not* exclude a file `dangerous-minds.md` in other locations.  It also does not exclude `a/b/posts/experiments/dangerous-minds.md`."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:221
