msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/po-translations.md:2
msgctxt "title"
msgid "PO Translations"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/po-translations.md:6
msgctxt "description"
msgid "Documents that are typically edited and modified many times during their life-cycle should better be translated in manageable chunks using a sophisticated translation workflow with a professional toolset."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/po-translations.md:8
msgid ""
"[% USE q = Qgoda %]\n"
"[% TAGS [@ @]%]\n"
"In such cases it is better to focus on the content in \n"
"the main language and manage the translations with the \n"
"normal\n"
"[translation workflow]([% q.llink(name=\"translation-workflow\")])."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/po-translations.md:15
msgid ""
"You will also find that necessary, when you let \n"
"translations be done by external translators as they \n"
"will not be very happy to edit markdown files."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/po-translations.md:19
msgid ""
"As an additional benefit, the translation process is \n"
"also cheaper and more efficient, even when you do the\n"
"translations yourself."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/po-translations.md:23
msgid ""
"[@ WRAPPER components/infobox.html\n"
"           type='info' title=\"It's Your Choice\" @]\n"
"Nobody forces you to use this approach for every document on your site. You\n"
"can switch between the two methods, whenever you see the need. You should\n"
"just keep in mind that switching from the\n"
"<a href=\"[@ q.llink(name='simple-content-translation') @]\">simple\n"
"approach</a> to the one described here using PO files will require manual work.\n"
"There is no way to get the translation from the translated markdown file into a\n"
"`.po` file.\n"
"[@ END @]"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/po-translations.md:34
msgid "## Trigger Documents"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/po-translations.md:36
msgid "The central idea of content inernationalization in Qgoda are so-called trigger documents.  They have no content \n"
"but only <q-term>front matter</q-term>:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/po-translations.md:39
msgid ""
"```yaml\n"
"---\n"
"master: /en/about-strawberries.md\n"
"lingua: de\n"
"title: √úber Erdbeeren\n"
"---\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/po-translations.md:47
msgid "The interesting variable here is `V:asset.master`. It just\n"
"points to the same document in the main language."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/po-translations.md:50
msgid ""
"The `V:asset.lingua` variable is also crucial to specify because Qgoda has to\n"
"know for which language it has to pull translations. But you normally specify\n"
"`V:asset.lingua` in the [defaults]([@ q.llink(name='defaults')@])\n"
"of your `P:_config.yaml`."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/po-translations.md:55
msgid ""
"All other variables that you add to the front matter are\n"
"just added to the document and available as regular\n"
"asset variables."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/po-translations.md:59
msgid "## Translating Front Matter"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/po-translations.md:61
msgid ""
"But you don't have to manually translated the front\n"
"matter from the original document. Instead you can\n"
"extract the relevant parts of it to the `.po`\n"
"file.  This is done with the special variable\n"
"`V:asset.translate`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/po-translations.md:67
msgid ""
"```yaml\n"
"---\n"
"master: /en/about-strawberries.md\n"
"translate:\n"
"    - title\n"
"    - description\n"
"---\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/po-translations.md:76
msgid ""
"This has the effect that the values of the front matter \n"
"variables `title` and `description` are extracted from\n"
"the master document into the `.po` file, and their \n"
"translations will be used, when generating the \n"
"translated document."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/po-translations.md:82
msgid ""
"[@ WRAPPER components/infobox.html\n"
"           type='info' title='Message Context' @]\n"
"All front-matter variables that get extracted will have the variable name\n"
"as their so-called message context. Identical strings with different \n"
"message contexts may have individual translations.\n"
"[@ END @]"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/po-translations.md:89
msgid ""
"You will normally always want to translate the same set of front matter\n"
"variables for every document. This is normally done by specifying\n"
"[defaults]([@ q.llink(name='defaults') @]):"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/po-translations.md:93
msgid ""
"```yaml\n"
"defaults:\n"
"  - files:\n"
"      - /*/**\n"
"    values:\n"
"      translate:\n"
"        - title\n"
"        - description\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/po-translations.md:103
msgid ""
"There is no problem specifying variables that don't appear in every one of\n"
"your documents. List entries that don't exist for a particular document are\n"
"simply ignored."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/po-translations.md:107
msgid ""
"[@ WRAPPER components/infobox.html\n"
"           type='warning' title='Do <em>not</em> translate <code>V:asset.name</code>!' @]\n"
"The variable <code>V:asset.name</code> is the constant link between language\n"
"versions. By assigning the same value to it for every language version of the\n"
"document, you can create references between them. If you translate it, the\n"
"mechanism will fail.\n"
"[@ END @]"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/po-translations.md:115 ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:126
msgid "## Missing Translations"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/po-translations.md:117 ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:128
msgid ""
"What if a certain string has not been \n"
"[translated]([@ q.llink(name='translation-workflow') @]) yet? The gettext way of\n"
"handling that situation is to use the original string, that is the string\n"
"in the main language of your site. That's not perfect but better than nothing\n"
"and you can always remedy it by providing a translation."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/po-translations.md:123
msgid "## What Else?"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/po-translations.md:125
msgid ""
"Nothing! It's as simple as that. Just set the\n"
"[defaults]([@ q.llink(name='defaults') @]) for `V:asset.translate` and\n"
"`V:asset.lingua` in `P:_config.yaml`. And then creating a translated version\n"
"of every document is as simple as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/po-translations.md:130
msgid ""
"```yaml\n"
"---\n"
"master: /en/qgoda-rocks.md\n"
"---\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/po-translations.md:136
msgid "This site itself is translated into German using exactly this technique."
msgstr ""

