#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:11
msgid "## The Command-Line Interface"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:13
msgid "Qgoda is a [command-line tool](http://www.guido-flohr.net/en/command-line/). Create an empty directory `qgoda-quickstart` somewhere and open a command-line window in it. Well-behaving command-line tools do not do anything destructive, when invoked without arguments.  Let's try whether qgoda is well-behaving:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:15
msgid ""
"```bash\n"
"qgoda-quickstart $ qgoda\n"
"qgoda: no command given!\n"
"Usage: qgoda COMMAND [OPTIONS]\n"
"Try 'qgoda --help' for more information!\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:22
msgid "Okay, do as you were told and try `qgoda --help`.  That will print out an overview of the things you can do with the program.  The command \"build\" looks promising.   Before you try it out, you can also get help for that specific command with `qgoda build --help`.  That will display a description of the command run through your system's pager.  Type `q` to close the page, because we will try it with learning by doing now."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:24
msgid ""
"```bash\n"
"qgoda-quickstart $ qgoda build\n"
"[warning][config] config file '_config.yaml' not found, proceeding with defaults.\n"
"[info][plugin-loader] initializing plug-ins.\n"
"[info] start building site\n"
"[info] finished building site with 0 artefacts\n"
"qgoda-quickstart $\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:33
msgid ""
"[% WRAPPER components/infobox.html\n"
"           type='info' title='Log Timestamps' %]\n"
"Actually, the log messages are prepended by timestamps.  They are discarded here, so that the log output is easier to read.\n"
"[% END %]"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:38
msgid "Did you notice the warning about the missing configuration file? What are these defaults that were mentioned in the warning? Try it out:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:40
msgid ""
"```bash\n"
"qgoda-quickstart $ qgoda config\n"
"---\n"
"case-sensitive: 0\n"
"defaults: []\n"
"exclude: []\n"
"exclude-watch: []\n"
"helpers: {}\n"
"index: index\n"
"latency: 0.5\n"
"location: /{directory}/{basename}/{index}{suffix}\n"
"...\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:54
msgid "Qgoda configuration is written in [YAML](http://www.yaml.org/), which is a more readable superset of [JSON](https://www.json.org/).  But since it is a strict superset, you can also write JSON, when you are more comfortable with JSON syntax.  You can also name the configuration file `P:_config.json` if you like."
msgstr ""

